title: Houston's warm up begins today ahead of a warm holiday week
text:
Recommended Videos
Today’s Forecast: HOUSTON – Winds will be breezy from the south at 10-15 mph gusting up to 20mph. This will help us warm up! Highs will be in the upper-70s and lower-80s under mostly sunny skies.
No description found Sunday’s Forecast: There is a small chance of showers on Sunday but not enough to make you cancel plans.
There is only around a 20% chance Outside of rain chances, expect mostly cloudy skies with temperatures reaching the 80s by the time Texans kick-off.
Texans tailgate is warm and cloudy Let's Go Texans! Your Extended Forecast: This warmth is not temporary! Houston stays above average through Christmas.
